Motion passed with a vote of 7 yes, 0 abstain, 0 missing

Joshua Drake pointed out that
<a href="https://www.postgresqlconference.org/">PostgreSQL Conference West</a>
had been announced and the Call For Papers was out.

Robert Brockway enquired about the fact that of 5 vacant seats only 4
had been filed; this takes the board down to 8 seats, which is the
minimum our bylaws allow.

There was some discussion about treating Debian and DebConf
separately, or at least providing details of money held for DebConf as a
line item within the Debian holding. It was pointed out DebConf is not
an SPI project and thus from our perspective it's all Debian's. There
were discussions around this topic already planned for DebConf.

Joe Nahmias expressed some concern at the poor rate of interest SPI
is receiving on assets that it holds. Michael Schultheiss said he would
research higher yield accounts.

